value.text: [Microsoft] did not want to deal with Sun Microsystems about the trademark issue, and so they called their implementation JScript. A lot of people think that JScript and JavaScript are different but similar languages. That's not the case. They are just different names for the same language, and the reason the names are different was to get around trademark issues.
Netscape and Sun announce JavaScript, the open, cross-platform object scripting language for enterprise networks and the internet
